{"title":"Specialized Celebrates XCC World Champions with Rainbow Stripe S-Works Epics","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/03/specialized-celebrates-xcc-world-champions-with-rainbow-stripe-s-works-epics/","date":1630695641000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-270401\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>The MTB World Championships in Val di Sole, Italy, was remarkable for the athletes and everyone watching. The battles and the upsets were truly electric in every discipline. For the first time, we saw XCC (short track) included in the MTB World Championships, and the races were ones for the history books.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123312/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-side-full-bike-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"eager\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123312/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-side-full-bike-.jpeg?ezimgfmt=rs%3Adevice%2Frscb28-1\" alt=\"S-Works World Champion Epics side full bike\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\"></a></p><h2>The Race</h2><p>Sina Frei (Switzerland), fresh off a silver medal at the Olympic games, showed up ready to ride in Val di Sole. The racecourse for the XXC was technical and required patience among the riders, go out too soon, and boom – explosion. Frie played it correctly, down to the wire, following crucial riders’ attacks and leading out the sprint from the final corner.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123302/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-lever-detail-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123302/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-lever-detail-.jpeg\" alt=\"S-Works World Champion Epics lever detail\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123302/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-lever-detail-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123302/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-lever-detail--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123302/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-lever-detail--120x80.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123302/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-lever-detail-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123302/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-lever-detail-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123302/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-lever-detail--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123302/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-lever-detail--120x80.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><p>The race came down to a perfect play of effort conservation, guts, and one heck of a photo finish with now XCO World Champion Evie Richards.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123257/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-front-of-full-bike-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123257/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-front-of-full-bike-.jpeg\" alt=\"S-Works World Champion Epics front of full bike\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123257/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-front-of-full-bike-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123257/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-front-of-full-bike--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123257/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-front-of-full-bike--120x80.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123257/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-front-of-full-bike-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123257/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-front-of-full-bike-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123257/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-front-of-full-bike--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123257/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-front-of-full-bike--120x80.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><p>Chris Blevins (United States) came into the XXC race final with confidence from a silver medal in the team relay and a front-row start along with the world’s best. He battled for every corner with Henrique Avancini (Brazil) and took the win in a glorious sprint that no one in the pack could match.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123246/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-crankset-detail-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123246/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-crankset-detail-.jpeg\" alt=\"S-Works World Champion Epics crankset detail\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123246/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-crankset-detail-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123246/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-crankset-detail--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123246/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-crankset-detail--120x80.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123246/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-crankset-detail-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123246/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-crankset-detail-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123246/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-crankset-detail--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123246/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-crankset-detail--120x80.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><p>Blevins would receive three medals in the MTB World Championships; a Gold medal in the XCC, a silver medal in the team relay, and a bronze medal in the E-Bike race. This medal achievement is the first time for any athlete at a world championship MTB event and the first American man to win in a cross country event since John Tomac in 1991.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123304/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-mixing-paint-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123304/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-mixing-paint-.jpeg\" alt=\"S-Works World Champion Epics mixing paint\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123304/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-mixing-paint-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123304/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-mixing-paint--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123304/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-mixing-paint--120x80.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123304/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-mixing-paint-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123304/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-mixing-paint-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123304/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-mixing-paint--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123304/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-mixing-paint--120x80.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><h2>Limited Edition S-Works World Champion Epics</h2><p>To recognize the outstanding performance of these incredible athletes, Specialized has created custom-painted S-Works Epic framesets, which they’ll pilot during their year in the World Champs jerseys.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123315/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-sticker-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123315/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-sticker-.jpeg\" alt=\"S-Works World Champion Epics sticker\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123315/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-sticker-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123315/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-sticker--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123315/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-sticker--120x80.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123315/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-sticker-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123315/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-sticker-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123315/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-sticker--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123315/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-sticker--120x80.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><p>If you want to share in the celebration but haven’t won a World Championship, you’re lucky — Specialized will be offering 50 limited edition framesets for riders to purchase in early October.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123306/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-paint-booth.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123306/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-paint-booth.jpeg\" alt=\"S-Works World Champion Epics paint booth\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123306/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-paint-booth.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123306/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-paint-booth-297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123306/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-paint-booth-120x80.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123306/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-paint-booth.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123306/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-paint-booth.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123306/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-paint-booth-297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123306/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-paint-booth-120x80.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><h2>OUTRIDE</h2><p>A portion of the World Champion Epic framesets proceeds will go to the OUTRIDE Foundation, an organization founded by Specialized Mike Sinyard and dedicated to proving that cycling benefits your brain. The program provides research, cycling programs, and grant-giving activities. “OUTRIDE provides evidence-based cycling interventions to improve social, emotional, and cognitive health.”</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123243/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-assembly-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123243/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-assembly-.jpeg\" alt=\"S-Works World Champion Epics assembly\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123243/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-assembly-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123243/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-assembly--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123243/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-assembly--120x80.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123243/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-assembly-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123243/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-assembly-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123243/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-assembly--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123243/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-assembly--120x80.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><h2>Next Stop Lenzerheide Sweden</h2><p>The next stop on the UCI MTB World Cup calendar is the historic track at Lenzerheide. This will be the first time we see the newly crowned World Champions in their respective trade team kits with all the cool bits.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123248/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-evade-helemt-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123248/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-evade-helemt-.jpeg\" alt=\"S-Works World Champion Epics custom evade helemt\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123248/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-evade-helemt-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123248/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-evade-helemt--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123248/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-evade-helemt--120x80.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123248/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-evade-helemt-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123248/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-evade-helemt-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123248/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-evade-helemt--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123248/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-evade-helemt--120x80.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><p>Specialized didn’t stop at the bikes, to help the champs match their new kits the paint team at Specialized crafted these one-off World Champion S-Works Evade helmets and S-Works Recon shoes.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123251/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-shoes-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123251/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-shoes-.jpeg\" alt=\"S-Works World Champion Epics custom shoes\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123251/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-shoes-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123251/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-shoes--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123251/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-shoes--120x80.jpeg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123251/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-shoes-.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123251/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-shoes-.jpeg 640w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123251/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-shoes--297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/03123251/S-Works-World-Champion-Epics-custom-shoes--120x80.jpeg 120w\"></a></p><p>For more information, check out <a href=\"https://www.specialized.com/us/en\">Specialized.com</a> frameset availability and <a href=\"https://outridebike.org/\">OUTRIDE for more info on local cycling programs</a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"2303f96ba5629c9a5fb36b192ec0d6b299d514b516250e38d576d647ddd61af3","category":"Cycling"}